Hello and thank you for this application.

Few weeks ago we have faced a problem of using captcha on our site. The use case is following: on desktop version of the site we needed to use default captcha widget, and on mobile devices - same widget but with different settings (font size, width, height).

As there are no possibility to use different configurations for captcha widgets, so i implemented it in an extension: https://github.com/asyncee/catpcha_extended

Extension is very simple - it overrides main view and adds possibility to load captcha widget settings through CAPTCHA_EXTENDED setting, so you can use different widgets like so:

```
CAPTCHA_EXTENDED = {
    'large': {
        'CAPTCHA_IMAGE_SIZE': (480, 50),
        'CAPTCHA_FONT_SIZE': 40,
    }
}

from captcha_extended.fields import CaptchaField

class MobileCommentForm(forms.Form):
    captcha = CaptchaField(config='large')
```

We use this extension in a number of our projects, but it would be nice if you can merge this implementation in django-simple-captcha, so any person can use it by default.
